review_text: The tunnel is long but it is very old.
If the abundance of homeless people that linger outside the metro aren't enough to deter you, the 10 minute long "iconic" moving walkway ride sure will.

I've been taking the Metro at Beaudry station daily for ten years.  Station entrance is modern and colorful, but underground isn't very clean and there are often homeless (though harmless) people sleeping on the seats, some of whom sometimes smoke. I've nicknamed this station "Hotel Beaudry".
Add hours to so people know when it opens and closes
It's not a stretch to call it the worst metro station in the city.
Love that place
Cool metro, colorful people. :3
Cool elevator
Closed for renovations until June 2019.
ALWAYS smells like sour vomit...
Metro station with one exit
Scary place after dark. Interest characters hang out here.

(Translated by Google) The renovations have been long but I think it will have been worth it.

(Original)
Les rénovations ont été longues mais je crois bien que ça l’aura valu la peine.

(Translated by Google) I stopped at this station for the first time in my life, to go to the Radio-Canada house ... I must admit that it is a foooooort pretty station! And this treadmill, I didn't even know it existed in metro stations!

(Original)
J'ai fait l'arrêt à cette station pour la première fois de ma vie, pour me rendre à la maison de Radio-Canada... Je dois avouer que c'est une foooooort jolie station! Et ce tapis roulant, je ne savais même pas que ça existait dans les stations de métro!

(Translated by Google) Following an 8-month closure, as of June 3, 2019, it opens to the public, while remaining under construction until March 2020. The only metro station with a long treadmill is to see but everything will be more beautiful at the end of the work.

(Original)
Suite à une fermeture de 8 mois, voilà qu'en date du 3 juin 2019, il ouvre au public, tout en restant en travaux jusqu'en mars 2020. La seule station de métro avec un long tapis roulant, c'est à voir, mais tout sera sûrement plus beau à la fin des travaux.

(Translated by Google) After the renovations. I got a taste in the elevator lol

(Translated by Google) Although the man who bequeathed his name to the station is not like the station, I think he would be proud of it since his neighborhood has kept its vitality. A stone's throw from the Berri-UQAM metro station, sometimes it's also quick to walk to get the distance.

(Original)
Bien que l'homme ayant légué son nom à la station ne soit pas à l'image de la station, je crois qu'il en serait fier puisque son quartier a su conserver sa vitalité. À deux pas du métro Berri-UQAM, parfois c'est aussi rapide de marcher pour faire la distance.

(Translated by Google) Interesting, well located, unpretentious. This would be the best place to put a water slide in Montreal. Missed opportunity in my opinion.

(Original)
Intéressant, bien situé, sans prétention. Ce serait la meilleure place pour y mettre une glissade d'eau à Montréal. Occasion ratée à mon avis.

(Translated by Google) To see after the renovations, but the resort is still mega deg! Dirty and often homeless junkies at the entrance!
